@@TJvAni.Animated
Description:
This property allows you to automatically change the frame. The delay between frames is controlled by the header of the ANI file, and if no information has been found, the default delay is 100 milliseconds.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAni.Author
Description:
This is the author of the ANI file. If not author is specified in the file, this property is blank.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAni.FramesCount
Description:
This property is the number of frames contained in the animation. If no animation has been opened or if the animation is empty, the value for this property is 0.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAni.Icon
Description:
This is the current icon showed in the animation. With this property, you can extract an icon from the animation. Use the property Index to choose the frame you want to see.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAni.Index
Description:
This property is the current index in the animation. When you modify this property, the property Iconi is modified and the frame selected is displayed. If the index is invalid, it does nothing !

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAni.Title
Description:
This is the title of the ANI file. If not title is specified in the file, this property is blank.

